    {
      "id": "02711ce9fcc0c656017e4c18977176c2376d2280",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-11-30 14:50:02.000000000",
      "message": "Change has been successfully cherry-picked as b1bec2c47aa597cf96e60840b8dd97125d782a03.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "0e2e6afd81e7af08d4424b029ed9d315a247e425",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-12-01 05:16:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI object to this workaround being landed.  If the problem is with a specific kernel version (< 2.6.33) and a specific test environment (LVM and/or inside a VM) the delay should be conditional on those factors.\n\nOtherwise we may be hiding all kind of other problems, either now or in the future, because we are testing in an environment that does not necessarily reflect normal usage (i.e. waiting 10s after mount before doing any operations).\n\nIn the past we had race conditions caused by clients creating MDS inodes with stripes on OSTs that they hadn't connected to yet, and they would get EIO when trying to write to the file.  I don't want to hide that kind of bug with such a sleep.\n\nThe other benefit of making the sleep conditional on the kernel version is that it will turn itself off once we update to newer kernels on the server.  We can't depend upon anyone to remember that this workaround is there and take it out at some point in the future, so at worst it will become a no-op check for some time before someone notices it and removes it.  The conditional check will make an \"active comment\" for the reader.\n\nPlease submit a follow-up patch which makes this timeout conditional.  It should also reference LU-482 as to why the timeout is there.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "f176625d88c9dd8d9699baedb574116500d5668d",
      "author": {
